history.content: You can gauge based on enrollment in prior semesters with https://berkeleytime.com/enrollment. Most people take the 10% rule (10% of class size will drop, so that percent will get enrolled from waitlist). For 189, you will have a lot more people enrolling because the ML hype is real, but you will have a lot of people dropping once they realize how painful ML theory can be sometimes, especially if they didn't take EECS 126/127. I also feel like 161 would be more likely to expand if need be than 189, but never bank on that
